==Trick-or-treating without the proper equipment==
'''Note:''' This section is shared with Man, Woman, Guard, Lumbridge Guide, Town Crier, Iffie, Elsie, and Ned.

* '''Player:''' Trick or treat!
* {{tcond|If the player does not have a treat cauldron:}}
** {{trandom}}
** {{topt|Dialogue 1}}
*** '''NPC:''' Spooky! But without a Treat cauldron, where will you store your treats?
*** {{tact|continues}}
** {{topt|Dialogue 2}}
*** '''NPC:''' I admire your spirit, but you can't go Trick-or- Treating without a Treat cauldron!
*** {{tact|continues}}
** {{tcond|If the player is not wearing at least three Halloween-themed items:}}
*** '''NPC:''' You also need to wear a spooky costume. At least three Halloween items should do the trick!
** '''NPC:''' Speak to the children near the west bank in Varrock, they'll help you get in the spooky spirit.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|If the player has less than three Halloween-themed items equipped:}}
** {{trandom}}
** {{topt|Dialogue 1}}
*** '''NPC:''' That's not a very spooky costume! Try combining at least three Halloween items, that'll be sure to spook!
** {{topt|Dialogue 2}}
*** '''NPC:''' Almost, but you can't go Trick-or-Treating without a spooky costume! At least three Halloween items should do the trick!
** '''NPC:''' Speak to the children near the west bank in Varrock, they'll help you get in the spooky spirit.
** {{tact|end}}

==Trick-or-treating event NPCs==
===Town Crier===
* '''Player:''' Trick or treat!
* {{tcond|If the player hasn't received treats from the town crier:}}
** '''Town Crier:''' Hear ye! Hear ye! Come and check out the spookiest costume in town!
** '''Player:''' Oh, where?
** '''Town Crier:''' Yours, of course, unless you tell me this isn't supposed to be a costume?
** '''Player:''' Oh it is! I am flattered!
** '''Town Crier:''' Then you hopefully won't mind me calling everyone to see it!
** '''Player:''' I appreciate the attention, although I was just really hoping for some treats!
** '''Town Crier:''' Straight to the point I see. Fine, please take these with my thanks! Have a happy Halloween!
** '''Player:''' Thank you! While I'm here, can you think of anyone else I should spook?
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{tcond|If the player has already received treats from the town crier:}}
** '''Town Crier:''' Ah, if it isn't the spookiest Trick-or-Treater!
** '''Player:''' Have you seen any better costumes?
** '''Town Crier:''' Why, are you looking for inspiration for next year?
** '''Player:''' Maybe? Possibly?
** '''Town Crier:''' I've seen quite a few good costumes but I still liked yours a lot. So as for next year, who can tell? Not me!
** '''Player:''' Fair enough then! Is anyone else giving out treats?
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{tcond|If the player has trick-or-treated everyone:}}
** '''Town Crier:''' I believe you've visited the most generous of us!
** '''Town Crier:''' The citizens are still as eager as ever, though, and I hear Varrock is the place to be for Trick-or-Treaters!
** {{tact|end}}
* {{trandom}}
* {{topt|cond=If the player has not yet talked to Elsie:|Dialogue 1}}
** '''Town Crier:''' You know, Elsie in the Varrock church loves a good spook as well! You should show her your costume!
* {{topt|cond=If the player has not yet talked to Iffie:|Dialogue 2}}
** '''Town Crier:''' You might like to pay Iffie in Varrock a visit. I hear she's being very generous with treats and stories!
* {{topt|cond=If the player has not yet talked to Ned:|Dialogue 3}}
** '''Town Crier:''' You know who else would love to see a colourful costume? Ned in Draynor Village!
* {{topt|cond=If the player has not yet talked to the Lumbridge Guide:|Dialogue 4}}
** '''Town Crier:''' I hear the Lumbridge Guide is welcoming all Trick-or- Treaters with a generous supply of treats!
* {{tact|end}}

===Elsie===
* '''Player:''' Trick or treat!
* {{tcond|If the player hasn't received treats from Elsie:}}
** '''Elsie:''' Oooh! What a lovely costume! You simply will have to show my sister Iffie later.
** '''Player:''' I somehow did not think Halloween was a holiday you'd enjoy.
** '''Elsie:''' Well dearie, appearances can be deceiving! Let me tell you a little story of my youth.
** '''Elsie:''' My sister and I have always loved knitting. Between Christmas jumpers and other wolly{{sic}} scarves, we have a little family tradition.
** '''Elsie:''' As a way to challenge ourselves, when we were a bit younger, we would knit the most horrifying Halloween costumes, then wear them and scare passers-by out of their wits!
** '''Player:''' What kind of costumes are we talking about?
** '''Elsie:''' Iffie's favourite costume represented the Chaos Elemental. Mine was a fearsome three-headed dragon!
** '''Player:''' Sorry, but I have to see it to believe it!
** '''Elsie:''' Sorry dearie! We were banned from wearing those years ago because of the mass hysteria they caused! I reused the yarn to make mittens for the church sale.
** '''Elsie:''' Anyway, thank you for taking the time to listen to my silly story. Have some well-deserved treats. They're not all mints, I promise.
** '''Player:''' Thank you Elsie! Do you know if anyone else is looking for some trick-or-treating fun?
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{tcond|If the player has already received treats from Elsie:}}
** '''Elsie:''' Hello dearie, are you here for another tale?
** '''Player:''' I suppose I could lend an ear.
** '''Elsie:''' Ok, a little short one then. One day a very kind adventurer came and brought me a warm cup of tea.
** '''Elsie:''' It's always nice to have a warm cup of tea, you know. Keeps the fingers nimble.
** '''Elsie:''' I was just telling them one of my stories when suddenly the biggest spider I had ever seen appeared in front of my eyes!
** '''Player:''' How big are we talking?
** '''Elsie:''' A spider that took the entirety of my field of vision! Bigger and fuzzier still than the ones you get near here.
** '''Player:''' Did the adventurer not help you out?
** '''Elsie:''' Unfortunately, they were busy being covered in tea. I had become rather startled, you see! Thankfully, all that movement caused the tiny spider to fall off my glasses!
** '''Player:''' I don't know if I would prefer a large spider far away or a small spider on my face!
** '''Player:''' I won't keep you any longer Elsie, but before I go, do you know of anyone that might have treats left?
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{tcond|If the player has trick-or-treated everyone:}}
** '''Elsie:''' I believe you've visited the most generous of us!
** '''Elsie:''' The citizens are still as eager as ever, though, and I hear Varrock is the place to be for Trick-or-Treaters!
** {{tact|end}}
* {{trandom}}
* {{topt|cond=If the player has not yet talked to Ned:|Dialogue 1}}
** '''Elsie:''' You know who else would love to see a colourful costume? Ned in Draynor Village!
* {{topt|cond=If the player has not yet talked to the Falador town crier:|Dialogue 2}}
** '''Elsie:''' I hear the Town crier in Falador loves a bit of Trick- or-Treating and has plenty of treats to hand out!
* {{topt|cond=If the player has not yet talked to Iffie:|Dialogue 3}}
** '''Elsie:''' You might like to pay my sister Iffie in the Varrock clothes shop a visit. I hear she's being very generous with treats and stories!
* {{topt|cond=If the player has not yet talked to the Lumbridge Guide:|Dialogue 4}}
** '''Elsie:''' I hear the Lumbridge Guide is welcoming all Trick-or- Treaters with a generous supply of treats!
* {{tact|end}}

===Iffie===
* '''Player:''' Trick or treat!
* {{tcond|If the player hasn't received treats from Iffie:}}
** '''Iffie:''' Oooh dearie! What a beautiful costume!
** {{tcond|If the player is wearing the [[ugly halloween jumper]], did not complete the [[2021 Halloween event]], and hasn't received treats from Iffie:}}
*** '''Iffie:''' What a beautiful jumper you have here. I remember once knitting one just like it! In fact, it could very well be this one!
*** {{tact|continue}}
** {{tcond|If the player is wearing the [[ugly halloween jumper]], completed the [[2021 Halloween event]], and hasn't received treats from Iffie:}}
*** '''Iffie:''' I am glad that you are still wearing that jumper I made for you! It still fits you perfectly, even two years on.
*** {{tact|continue}}
** {{tcond|If the above two conditions are not met:}}
*** '''Iffie:''' I would have jumped out of my skin if I could still jump.
*** {{tact|continue}}
** '''Iffie:''' Say, while you're here, would you care for a scary story?
** '''Player:''' Sure, why not!
** '''Iffie:''' We have bowls of treats we keep to treat Trick-or- Treaters. We left the bowls outside the shop so the Trick-or-Treaters wouldn't come in and frighten the customers.
** '''Iffie:''' However we found the treats vanishing in an instant, as if a greedy passer-by would help themselves without leaving any for anyone else.
** '''Iffie:''' That's not very polite if you ask me. I was ready to be up in arms about today's youth, but I thought it would be prudent to witness the thief first.
** '''Player:''' That sounds dangerous! What did you do?
** '''Iffie:''' We refilled the bowls and waited, but we must have been too visible. Everyone was behaving perfectly. We went to sit back and the sweets vanished once again!
** '''Player:''' Was it ghosts? I bet it was ghosts.
** '''Iffie:''' We refilled again and this time hid very carefully. For a while nothing happened. Charlie came by, but he only took a couple of sweets before strolling back.
** '''Iffie:''' Then when we least expected it, the most unsettling monster appeared from behind the shop, crammed its head into one of the bowls and wolfed the whole contents out!
** '''Player:''' Oh no! What did it look like?
** '''Iffie:''' Knee-height, eyes as dark as the night, a large gaping mouth, four legs, skin peeling and covered in fleas!
** '''Iffie:''' Eventually we understood that someone had been putting Halloween costumes on the hungry stray dogs! We now keep the bowls where we can see them!
** '''Player:''' Oh, I was not expecting that plot twist!
** '''Player:''' That was a lovely story, Iffie. Before I take my leave, is there anyone else I should visit?
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{tcond|If the player has already received treats from Iffie:}}
** '''Iffie:''' So, did you spot the spookiest stray dogs?
** '''Player:''' I know they lurk around here and am in no rush to find them!
** '''Iffie:''' I saw one dressed as a huge spider earlier!
** '''Iffie:''' I can add that to my list of jumpers I ought to try knitting.
** '''Player:''' What, a jumper featuring a dog dressed as a spider? That sounds ambitious!
** '''Iffie:''' Or maybe just spider-themed. Maybe next year, who knows!
** '''Player:''' While I'm here, do you know of anyone else giving out treats?
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{tcond|If the player has trick-or-treated everyone:}}
** '''Iffie:''' I believe you've visited the most generous of us!
** '''Iffie:''' The citizens are still eager as ever, though, and I hear Varrock is the place to be for Trick-or-Treaters!
** {{tact|end}}
