===Lumbridge Guide===
* '''Player:''' Trick or treat!
* {{tcond|If the player hasn't received treats from the Lumbridge Guide:}}
** '''Lumbridge Guide:''' Greetings, adventurer! Are you looking for advice or are you looking for treats?
** '''Player:''' Can you guess from looking at my outfit?
** '''Lumbridge Guide:''' I have seen adventurers sporting a wide range of interesting get-ups no matter the season.
** '''Lumbridge Guide:''' This said, it's the season to be spooky and you do a fine job of it!
** '''Lumbridge Guide:''' I will not ask whether this is also your choice of clothes the rest of the year.
** '''Lumbridge Guide:''' After all, you are more than welcome to dress how you like, when you like.
** '''Player:''' That is very accepting of you!
** '''Lumbridge Guide:''' I meet a lot of people in my line of work and hear a lot of stories. Believe it or not, people tell stories of adventures, past and future, just by the way they dress.
** '''Player:''' And what does my outfit say?
** '''Lumbridge Guide:''' That you are very interested in gathering sweet treats!
** '''Player:''' You're spot on! While we're on the topic, is there anyone else I should visit?
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{tcond|If the player has already received treats from the Lumbridge Guide:}}
** '''Lumbridge Guide:''' Hello again! Are you looking for advice or are you looking for treats?
** '''Player:''' I would take more treats if you're offering!
** '''Lumbridge Guide:''' I should have expected this! I will have to admit that my treat supply is limited and I have many more adventurers to reward.
** '''Player:''' I suppose that is fair enough. In that case, I will take your advice to help me find someone else to visit!
** {{tact|continues}}
